          {
            "text": "Mix and bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C (180°C fan). Rub {{unsalted-butter}} into {{self-raising-flour}} until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Stir in {{caster-sugar}} and {{mixed-spice}}, then fold through {{currants}} and {{mixed-peel}} if using. Add the beaten {{eggs}} and {{whole-milk}} and mix to a stiff, rough mixture. It should hold its shape when heaped but not be smooth. Spoon 12 rough mounds onto lined baking trays, leaving 4 cm between them. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes until the peaks are golden and the edges are set. Cool on a wire rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
